## Local overrides for self-host testing (example)
#
# Copy to `hosting/docker/.env.local` and edit values:
#   cp hosting/docker/.env.local.example hosting/docker/.env.local
#
# Then run with both env files:
#   docker compose --env-file .env --env-file .env.local -f docker-compose.yaml -f docker-compose.local.yaml up -d --build core ollama
#
# Notes:
# - `OPENAI_API_KEY` is required by the SDK. For many OpenAI-compatible proxies, any non-empty value works.
# - This example routes chat to an OpenAI-compatible proxy and embeddings to Ollama.
# - `EMBEDDING_MODEL_SIZE` must match your pgvector schema/index dimension. Many stacks default to 1536.
#
# Chat via OpenAI-compatible proxy:
OPENAI_API_KEY=proxy
OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://YOUR_PROXY_HOST:PORT/v1
OPENAI_API_MODE=chat_completions
CHAT_PROVIDER=openai
MODEL=gpt-5.2

# Embeddings via Ollama:
OLLAMA_URL=http://ollama:11434
EMBEDDINGS_PROVIDER=ollama
EMBEDDING_MODEL=mxbai-embed-large
EMBEDDING_MODEL_SIZE=1536

# If you ever switch to Ollama chat:
# CHAT_PROVIDER=ollama
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llama3.2:1b
